    {
      "id": "ii_UcYNW1dz5wMLJyYeIH",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2186.2400109330943,
      "y": -158.2060845693692,
      "width": 833.1992797851562,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b13",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1885746308,
      "version": 1630,
      "versionNonce": 942791428,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1780141183122,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\n1) We initiated a transaction but no response from external network so we retry leading to double charges\n2) Payment succeeded but we don't update in our DB the same and we don't notify the Merchant\n\n- Worst is to consider a timeout to be transaction failed.\n\n- Set status as verification-pending and then call the PaymentNetwork to check if payment has been\nconfirmed. Else we need a cron-job that runs evey few mins to check on the payments. But running \nthe cron every few mins leads to customers waiting for their payments. For this we need to query DB\nfor pending transactions with an index on Status column.\n\n- When we didn't get results from PaymentNetwork within 5secs we set the staus to timeout\nand then this event gets pushed to Kafka stream via CDC which is read by some workers\nto check pending payments. (Kafka is pull based commit log). We create separate topics \nfor timed out transactions and then retry, get the update and write to DB, then also store in S3.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\n1) We initiated a transaction but no response from external network so we retry leading to double charges\n2) Payment succeeded but we don't update in our DB the same and we don't notify the Merchant\n\n- Worst is to consider a timeout to be transaction failed.\n\n- Set status as verification-pending and then call the PaymentNetwork to check if payment has been\nconfirmed. Else we need a cron-job that runs evey few mins to check on the payments. But running \nthe cron every few mins leads to customers waiting for their payments. For this we need to query DB\nfor pending transactions with an index on Status column.\n\n- When we didn't get results from PaymentNetwork within 5secs we set the staus to timeout\nand then this event gets pushed to Kafka stream via CDC which is read by some workers\nto check pending payments. (Kafka is pull based commit log). We create separate topics \nfor timed out transactions and then retry, get the update and write to DB, then also store in S3.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
